<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 State Attorney General <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> <PERSON> Celebrezze </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, a leading contender for the Democratic gubernatorial nomination, announced a shift in his position on abortion, angering anti-abortion activists. <PERSON> Celebrezze </PERSON>, who had voiced a strong anti-abortion position since entering the state <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> in 1975, told reporters Saturday he supports public funding of abortions for low-income women and would veto legislation to ban abortion. <PERSON> Celebrezze </PERSON> said he now believes women should have the right to choose abortion until the fetus is determined to be viable, at which point the rights of the fetus become paramount. The switch comes amid growing evidence that a strong anti-abortion stance can be a political liability. Abortion played a prominent role in the recent gubernatorial races in <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>, and pro-choice candidates won both elections. <PERSON> Celebrezze </PERSON> was expected to announce his candidacy later this month for the Democratic primary to be held in May. `` My own beliefs lead me to conclude that abortion is almost always the wrong solution to the problem of unwanted pregnancy,'' he said. `` Public officials, however, have a special obligation to explain what role the government they serve ought to play in the abortion decision.'' But <PERSON> Curt </PERSON> <PERSON> Steiner </PERSON>, spokesman for Republican gubernatorial candidate <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Voinovich </PERSON>, who opposes abortion, said <PERSON> Celebrezze </PERSON> ca n't have it both ways. `` I think this is a shocking reversal. Here's a person who says he wants to run on his record, then the first thing he does is run away from his record,'' he said. <PERSON> Jill </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Spangler </PERSON>, executive director of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZ