N> was dictated by history and that <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> should remain part of the Soviet-led <ORGANIZATION> Warsaw </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pact </ORGANIZATION>. `` I think his view was one of ... caution,'' <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said. `` I really believe that. I think he recognized the rapidity of change. He has very constructively talked about peaceful change.'' `` I think he feels that if there were outside forces setting dates that would complicate the way he is helping manage the change in the pact,'' <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> added.
