<HEAD>Truck Crash Kills 19, Including 8 Members of Soccer Team</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIMA, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Eight members of a soccer team, a club official and 10 fans were killed when their truck careened off a road in the desert 225 miles southeast of <LOCATION> Lima </LOCATION>, police said Monday. The accident occurred Sunday night when the truck's brakes failed, according to the police report. The other 21 people aboard the vehicle, all of them players or fans, were injured, including several seriously. The players belonged a soccer team from a local agricultural cooperative that had defeated a rival team in nearby <LOCATION> Nazca </LOCATION>, a town renown for strangely designed lines in the desert that include huge drawings of birds. The team and fans were returning home when the accident occurred, police said.
