of anti-corruption investigations and 12 former leaders have been expelled from the party. Opposition members urged citizens during a news conference Monday to `` block coverup attempts and illegal removals'' of documents and other items. <PERSON> Lothar </PERSON> <PERSON> Scharsich </PERSON>, spokesman for the opposition group <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Forum </ORGANIZATION>, also pleaded for `` no violence.'' In <LOCATION> Bonn </LOCATION>, the chief aide to Chancellor <PERSON> Helmut </PERSON> <PERSON> Kohl </PERSON> of <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> said the East German party was `` incapable of acting'' and had `` totally lost the trust of its supporters, its members and the people.'' <PERSON> Rudolf </PERSON> <PERSON> Seiters </PERSON> has been negotiating with with East German leaders on financial aid, in exchange for which <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> demands free elections and economic reform, and laying the groundwork for a visit by <PERSON> Kohl </PERSON> to <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>.
