 `` How I Got Into College'' -LRB- CBS-Fox Video. VHS-Beta, $ 89.98. Rated PG-13. -RRB- <PERSON> Marlon </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON>, a rather dim high school student who bombs out on his SATs, nevertheless sets his sights on getting into selective <ORGANIZATION> Ramsey </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> College </ORGANIZATION> to be near the girl he loves from afar, <PERSON> Jessica </PERSON> <PERSON> Kailo </PERSON> _ scholar, cheerleader and class president. Will Marlon -LRB- <PERSON> Corey </PERSON> <PERSON> Parker </PERSON> -RRB- get into <PERSON> Ramsey </PERSON>? Will he win the girl of his dreams? <PERSON> Will </PERSON> <PERSON> Jessica </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Lara </PERSON> <PERSON> Flynn </PERSON> <PERSON> Boyle </PERSON> -RRB- get into <PERSON> Ramsey </PERSON>? A high school guidance counselor might call `` How I Got Into College'' an underachiever. Consider the potential for a movie about getting into college _ the terror of taking the SATs, confusion over where to apply, the dreaded college interview, the agonizing wait for word of whether you've been admitted or rejected. `` How I Got Into College,'' a comedy, tries to take on all this, but does it with little humor, drama or insight. It has some clever spots _ a shady SAT coaching service; a mailman bringing a letter with a demonic grin; students phoning home frantically to find out whether they've received a fat letter -LRB- an acceptance -RRB- or a thin one -LRB- a rejection -RRB-. But the movie often substitutes offbeat camera angles for humor, and the odd-couple romance is n't particularly compelling. By the end, it's clear <PERSON> Marlon </PERSON> has more to offer than we thought. But not much more. Send `` How I Got Into College'' a thin letter. _ By <PERSON> Pete </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> Writer.
