 Places to go, things to see and do, travel bargains to have: _ The sixth edition of `` Where to Find It, Buy It, Eat It in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>'' by <PERSON> Gerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> has been updated to cover the latest in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> dining, shopping, sightseeing and hotels. The author, who lives in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> but spends weekends in <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION>, lists 220 places in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> he considers best and also includes a negative list of what he calls `` Do n't Bother Restaurants.'' He also tells how to get tickets to shows and which are the best museums, where the bargains can be found in discount and off-price stores, and where, if you need one, to find a chimney sweep. Also included are instructions on how to find addresses and read maps and how to get around the big town. _ _ A new blues and gospel pavilion opens in December in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Orleans </LOCATION>, featuring two nightly performances of gospel, followed by three blues sessions. Located between two Creole cottages at 227 Bourbon Street, the pavilion will spotlight local and national artists, with sessions beginning at 8 p.m. and continuing until 2 a.m. every night, beginning in January. The pavilion will be open weekends for the inaugural month of December. _ Starting in March, rail buffs can make a Oakland-Los Angeles run in the Princess' Super Dome rail cars which will be attached to <ORGANIZATION> Amtrak </ORGANIZATION>'s Coast Starlight trains No. 11 and 14. The trains will be called `` <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sun </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION>,'' with passengers able to make the entire trip in one day or to choose an overnight stopover at <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Luis </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Obispo </LOCATION>. The luxury dome cars, privately owned by Princess, already operate through <LOCATION> Alaska </LOCATION> through the company's <ORGANIZATION> Tour </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alaska </ORGANIZATION> subsidiary. The cars will be outfitted in oak, brass, plush carpeting and wool upholstery, topped by curved plate glass windows. Chefs will prepare food on board, served in a dining salon with linen, fine china and French stemware. _ An ancient bayou, the great <LOCATION> Chacahoula </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Swamp </LOCATION>, is venue for day trips operated by the <LOCATION> Atchfalaya </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Basin </LOCATION> Backwater Adventure in <LOCATION> Gibson </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> La </LOCATION>. The tours explore areas with ancient cypress trees and exotic wildlife in what was the main exit of the <LOCATION> Mississippi </LOCATION> into the <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> 5,000 to 10,000 years ago. The tour boats travel through rugged terrain on normally non-navigable waterways. _ For a room with a really different view, try the <ORGANIZATION> Undersea </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lodge </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Key </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Largo </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla </LOCATION>. It's billed as the world's only underwater hotel, with views looking out on the water 30 feet below the lagoon at the new Key Largo Undersea Park. The park enables visitors to accompany professionals exploring the remains of a shipwreck, study and swim with more than 100 marine life species, and learn about marine conservation. _ Five historic sites in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Hudson </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION> are clustered along the river north of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> and can be taken in with day drives or train trips from a <LOCATION> Westchester </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> touring base. <PERSON> Washington </PERSON> <PERSON> Irving </PERSON>'s home at <LOCATION> Sunnyside </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> Sleepy </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hollow </LOCATION> area he wrote about, the water-powered grist mill and house at <LOCATION> Philipsburg </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Manor </LOCATION>, the 18th century <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> Cortlandt </PERSON> <PERSON> Manor </PERSON>, and the <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pocantico </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hills </ORGANIZATION> with stained glass windows by <PERSON> Henri </PERSON> <PERSON> Matisse </PERSON> and <PERSON> Marc </PERSON> <PERSON> Chagall </PERSON> all are within minutes of each other along Route 9 in the <LOCATION> Tarrytown </LOCATION> area. <LOCATION> Montgomery </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Place </LOCATION>, at <LOCATION> Annandale-on-Hudson </LOCATION> near <LOCATION> Kingston </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION>, is a restoration in progress. The manor is the ancestral home of the <LOCATION> Hudson </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION>'s <PERSON> Livingston </PERSON> family and commands views of the river and the <LOCATION> Catskill </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mountains </LOCATION>. The properties are are managed by Historic <LOCATION> Hudson </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Tarrytown </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION> _ <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Carnival </ORGANIZATION>, or `` Fasching,'' starts before Christmas and goes on through Ash Wednesday, offering American travelers the chance to take part in the public celebrations such as Rose Monday in <LOCATION> Cologne </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Dusseldorf </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Mainz </LOCATION>, or the `` <LOCATION> Munich </LOCATION> Crazy'' celebration. Travel costs in <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> are lower during the winter, according to the <ORGANIZATION> German </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZAT