<HEAD>U.S. Appeals Court Upholds Judgment Against DeLorean</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CINCINNATI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A federal appeals court ruled Monday that a British court's award of a $ 54 million default judgment against former automaker <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Z. </PERSON> <PERSON> DeLorean </PERSON> can be enforced against him. A three-judge panel of the 6th U.S. <ORGANIZATION> Circuit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Appeals </ORGANIZATION> upheld a lower court's ruling against <PERSON> DeLorean </PERSON>, who tried to prevent enforcement of the British court's award. Last month in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, however, <ORGANIZATION> English </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> High </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> Judge <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Gibson </PERSON> overturned a lower court order that allowed legal documents in the case to be served on <PERSON> DeLorean </PERSON> at his home in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>, outside the jurisdiction of the English courts. `` It follows that all subsequent orders made against Mr. <PERSON> DeLorean </PERSON> will fall away,'' <PERSON> Gibson </PERSON> said in his Nov. 24 ruling. In October 1987, the <ORGANIZATION> High </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Chancery </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> division in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> awarded the default judgment against <PERSON> DeLorean </PERSON> to <ORGANIZATION> DSQ </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Property </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. Ltd.. DSQ Property, formerly <ORGANIZATION> DeLorean </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cars </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Belfast </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Northern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION>, then sued in January 1989 in federal court in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOC