Ltd. </ORGANIZATION> was created as the corporate successor to <ORGANIZATION> DeLorean </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cars </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION>, which went into financial receivership The British court's judgment and DeLorean's settlement with the bankruptcy trustee of <ORGANIZATION> DeLorean </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, which filed for bankruptcy in October 1982, resulted from claims involving the design of the DeLorean automobile. The 6th Circuit appellate court rejected <PERSON> DeLorean </PERSON>'s arguments that his settlement with the bankruptcy trustee prevented recognition or enforcement of the British court's award in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. The court also rejected <PERSON> DeLorean </PERSON>'s arguments that he had not been properly served with documents to inform him of the British court's award. <PERSON> Morganroth </PERSON> said he expects DSQ Property to appeal the British court's ruling.
